[h4 
	" The last battle begins
	$LF
]h4
[h4 
	" Tomator Phase 1.
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Erik used item duplication glitch to get third bomb from left side and saved about 2 seconds.
	$LF
	"The presence of Olaf is not necessary for remaining phases, so instead teleportation he prefer having fun jumping on trampoline until end of game. Switched to Baleog as soon as yellow key was used.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Tomator Phase 2.
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"While lift is moving up switched to Erik, Erik execute door clip.
	$LF
	"After shooting into switches presence of Baleog is not necessary for remaining phases, so possible to skip blue key and all other Baleog actions.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Tomator Phase 3.
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"This phase is the most significant moment for sequence breaking. Erik use cocktail of various tricks and glitches:
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Passed both force fields off screen, and turn off them. With using to item duplication glitch get three shields.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Bash Tomator at moment of appearing to divide him and his private force field - now our enemy is defenseless and Erik can push him to anti-gravity field which force him to teleport him the directly to Phase 5.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"To cancel side effect of bashing use special technique to penetrate inside Tomato and get damage just after bashing him. Used all 3 shields and 2 standard HP to cancel it 5 times.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Tomator Phase 4.
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Skipped.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Tomator Phase 5.
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Actually it is not Phase 5, it is continue of Phase 3, Tomator just teleported here.
	$LF
	"Between P3 and P5 there is significant difference. In normal Phase 5 Tomator can't walk. But we still have deal with dangerous opponent from P3  - he CAN walk. And in case if he will walk enough far from lever - it lead to unpleasant complication, he will not fly when Erik will shut down the lever. So to be able send Tomator into space without extra complications, Erik must run as fast as the wind. And he did it.
	$LF
]p
